Claims 1. A method of installing an alarm sensor in a door attached to a door frame, comprising the steps of: (a) providing a positioning member, the positioning member having a longitudinal centerline and a marking point, the marking point being aligned with the longitudinal centerline of the positioning member, and the positioning member including a pair of longitudinal grooves and lower open areas; (b) partially opening the door; (c) placing the positioning member in a hole in the frame, the positioning member having a longitudinal centerline and a bore which is passes through the longitudinal centerline; (d) while the positioning member is at least partially located in the hole, closing the door in the door frame; (e) while the door is closed in the door frame, applying force on the positioning member to cause the marking point of the positioning member to make a positioning mark on the door; (f) after step "e", opening the door and removing the positioning member from the hole in the frame; and (g) after step "e", drilling an opening in the door at the location of the positioning mark. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein in the step "d", the door is pivotally connected to the frame. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein during step "d", the door is slidably connected to the frame and the closing of the door in the frame requires the door to slide parallel to the frame while the door is substantially parallel to the frame. 4. The method of claim 1, wherein the positioning mark is an indentation. 5. The method of claim 1, wherein during step "d" and before step "e", the door is partially opened, causing the positioning mark to be an extended mark or line. 6. The method of claim 1, wherein in the step "a", the positioning member has a rounded tip, and in step "c" the rounded tip is placed in the hole. 7. The method of claim 1, wherein in the step "a", the positioning member has a positioning surface which is cylindrically shaped and has an outer diameter which is slightly smaller than the hole in the frame, and in step "c" the positioning surface is placed in the hole. 8. The method of claim 1, wherein during step "e", the mark is made on marking material which is of a different material than the door. 9. The method of claim 8, wherein the marking material is a foam. 10. The method of claim 8, wherein the marking material has a thickness of at least 1 millimeter. 11. The method of claim 1 , wherein in the step "a", the positioning member is cylindrically, conically, or frustoconically shaped. 12. The method of claim 1, wherein in the step "a", the positioning member is attached to a flexible member, and in step "e" force is applied to the flexible member to cause the positioning mark. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein the positioning member includes a plurality of longitudinal recesses which connect to the bore. 14. The method of claim 12, wherein the flexible member is selected from the group consisting of a rope, wire, chain, cord, or string. 15. The method of claim 12, wherein the flexible member is a cord. 16. A method of installing a door locking system, comprising the steps of: (a) providing a positioning member, the positioning member having a longitudinal centerline and a marking point, the marking point being aligned with the longitudinal centerline of the positioning member, a bore which is passes through the longitudinal centerline and a pair of longitudinal grooves and lower open areas; (b) partially opening the door; (c) placing the positioning member in a hole in the door; (d) while the positioning member is at least partially located in the hole, closing the door in the door frame; (e) while the door is closed in the door frame, applying force on the positioning member to cause the marking point of the positioning member to make a positioning mark on the frame; 

